<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-8146] Fix validation of collections in TriggerExecutor</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-8146</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;TriggerExecutor.validate uses o.a.c.cql.QueryProcessor (i.e. the cql2 version) to validate cells in generated mutations. This suffers from the same issue with collections as described in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7665&quot; title=&quot;nodetool scrub fails on system schema with UDTs&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-7665&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-7665&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With cql2 being removed in 3.0, TriggerExecutor in trunk does the right thing and uses the Cell&apos;s validateFields method, so we should just do the same thing in 2.1.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
